job.title: OPSC Post Graduate Teacher Online Form 2021
job.body:
Total Vacancies:139

 

Description:

The Odisha Public Service Commission (OPSC) issued a total of 139 vacancies for the posts of Post Graduate Teacher. The online application for the posts of Post Graduate Teacher under the Odisha Public Service Commission (OPSC)  shall start from 24-03-2021. The eligible candidates must submit the online application before 23-04-2021. Check the complete details below so that all the doubts about the filling of the online application get cleared. For more such updates do visit theprograd.com .The ProGrad jobs.

 

Mode of application & application fee:

The mode of application is online and after filling in the required details you have to provide the billing details for the application fee.

  • No application fee for the SC, ST of Odisha, PwD.
  • The application fee for others is Rs. 500
  • For more details, you can refer to the notification. The link is given at the bottom.

Important dates:

  • The Starting date to apply for this online application form is 24-03-2021
  • The Last date to apply for this online application form is 23-04-2021
  • Last Date for Submission of Online Application: 30-04-2021

Educational qualification required:

To apply for the posts issued by the Odisha Public Service Commission (OPSC)  you must have fallen in the educational criteria given below:

  • Candidates Should Possess Master Degree/ M.Sc, B.Ed to apply for the post of Post Graduate Teacher  

Age limit criteria:

  • To apply for this job you must have fallen in the age limit criteria provided by the Odisha Public Service Commission (OPSC)  :
  • The minimum age limit to apply is 21 Years
  • The maximum age limit to apply is 32 Years
  • Candidates he/ she must have been born not earlier than 02-01-1989 & not later than 01-01-2000
  • For age relaxation criteria you can refer to the notification given below in The ProGrad jobs.

Pay Scale:

  • The pay scale as per 7th pay commission for the post of Post Graduate Teacher is 45000/month
  • Check the detailed notification also if we missed something

Detailed vacancies:

The vacancies in detail are given below. Check below that Odisha Public Service Commission (OPSC) issued this notification for which posts.

 

How to apply for OPSC Post Graduate Teacher Online Form 2021?

  • First, visit the official website.
  • Register yourself on the portal of the Odisha Public Service Commission (OPSC).
  • Login yourself on the portal.
  • Find the notification of Post Graduate Teacher.
  • Fill up the complete details that are asked in the application form.
  • Upload your photo and signature with the dimensions asked in the instructions.
  • Submit the application fee
  • Finally, download the application form for future needs.

How to prepare for this exam?

Try this strategy to crack any exam:

  • You must have the syllabus.
  • Give a brief reading of the syllabus.
  • Buy a previous year's papers book.
  • See the most frequent topics that came in previous papers.
  • First, finish them and revise them on daily basis.
  • Recommended books to crack this exam.
  • The final and most important steps are to revise, revise and revise.
